.TH NADRIAN 1 "2023-04-24" "1.0" "nadrian man page"

.SH NADRIAN
Nadrian - a simple command-line shell

.SH SYNOPSIS
#include "simple_shell.h"
.TP
\fB./hsh\fR

.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBNadrian\fR is a simple command-line shell that allows users to execute commands and interact with their system. It supports basic shell features such as input/output redirection, piping, and command chaining.

.SH COMMANDS
.TP
\fBcd\fR [\fIDIRECTORY\fR]
Change the current working directory to \fIDIRECTORY\fR. If \fIDIRECTORY\fR is not specified, change to the home directory.
.TP
\fBls\fR [\fIDIRECTORY\fR]
List the contents of \fIDIRECTORY\fR. If \fIDIRECTORY\fR is not specified, list the contents of the current directory.
.TP
\fBecho\fR [\fISTRING\fR]
Print \fISTRING\fR to the standard output.
.TP
\fBpwd\fR
Print the current working directory.
.TP
\fBexit\fR
Exit the shell.

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
\fB$ ls\fR
.TP
\fIfile1.txt\fR
.TP
\fIfile2.txt\fR
.TP
\fBdir1\fR
.TP
\fBdir2\fR
.TP
\fB$ cd dir1\fR
.TP
\fB$ pwd\fR
.TP
/Users/user/dir1
.TP
\fB$ cd ..\fR
.TP
\fB$ pwd\fR
.TP
/Users/user

.SH AUTHOR
